explanation: process_params itself does not call memcmp, but it dispatches argument strings to other functions that may compare option names or argument text. To determine whether any comparison of null‑terminated strings is performed using memcmp (a MISRA violation), the bodies of all callees that receive argv strings must be inspected: process_long_param and its specific long‑option handlers (process_param__*), process_short_params_str and the short‑option handler process_short_param, and the string-to‑uint helper mhd_tool_str_to_uint (in case it uses memcmp internally). Also include the standard library symbol memcmp so the analysis can detect direct or indirect uses of memcmp (calls or wrappers) in any of these functions.
